      <hedline>
        <hl1>Kael's Fate</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Former editor Robert Stein letter on Kristin Hohenade's August 27 assertion that Pauline Kael's review of Sound of Music cost her job at McCall's (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Sorry to be a spoilsport, but Pauline Kael's review of ''The Sound of Music'' in McCall's was not what cost her the job [''All Together Now: The Hills Are Still Alive . . .'' by Kristin Hohenadel, Aug. 27]. I was the magazine's editor at the time and rather liked her trashing it as ''The Sound of Money.'' I gave up months later after she kept panning every commercial movie from ''Lawrence of Arabia'' and ''Dr. Zhivago'' to ''The Pawnbroker'' and ''A Hard Day's Night.''</p>
        <p>ROBERT STEIN  Barrytown, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
